(930, 1, '2016-03-02 07:54:25', '2016-03-02 07:54:25', 'Advertisers have attempted to quantify and qualify the use of celebrities in their marketing campaigns by evaluating the awareness generated, appeal, and relevance to a brand''s image and the celebrity''s influence on consumer buying behavior.\r\n\r\nSocial media such as Twitter have become[when?] increasingly[quantify] popular mediums for celebrities to endorse brands and to attempt to influence purchasing behavior. According to Bloomberg News, social-media-ad spending was expected[by whom?] to reach a total of $4.8 billion at the end of 2012 and $9.8 billion by 2016.[1] Advertising and marketing companies sponsor celebrities to tweet and influence thousands (sometimes millions) of their followers to buy brand products. For example, Ryan Seacrest (an American broadcaster) gets paid to promote Ford products.[2] Companies that pay celebs to tweet for them subscribe to the Malcolm Gladwell theory of influence[clarification needed].[citation needed]\r\n\r\nCelebrity endorsements have proven very successful in China, where increasing consumerism makes the purchase of an endorsed product into a status symbol. On August 1, 2007, laws were passed banning healthcare professionals and public figures such as movie stars or pop singers from appearing in advertisements for drugs or nutritional supplements. A spokesperson stated, "A celebrity appearing in drug advertising is more likely to mislead consumers, therefore, the state must consider controlling medical advertisements and strengthen the management of national celebrities appearing in medical advertisements."[citation needed]', 'celebrity testimonial', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'celebrity-testimonial', '', '', '2016-03-02 10:56:37', '2016-03-02 10:56:37', '', 0, 'http://switchedon.addwebprojects.com/?post_type=testimonials-widget&#038;p=930', 0, 'testimonials-widget', '', 0),
(931, 1, '2016-03-02 09:53:23', '2016-03-02 09:53:23', '[vc_row full_height="yes" fullwidth="1" nospacing="1" el_class="custom-slider-home1" css=".vc_custom_1455689540254{padding-left: 0px !important;}"][vc_column width="3/4"][rev_slider_vc alias="home-page"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4" el_class="custom-slider-aboutme"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>About Me</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="700" img_size="190 x 190" style="vc_box_circle_2" css=".vc_custom_1456138289119{border-radius: 1px !important;}" el_class="custom-about-circle"][vc_column_text]I wanted to be an actress when I was younger. My parents thought that wasn''t very sensible, so I ended up studying law instead.[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="CONTINUE READING" style="flat" shape="square" color="inverse" size="xs" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fswitchedon.addwebprojects.com%2Fabout-me%2F|title:About%20me|target:%20_blank"][vc_raw_html]JTNDaHIlMjAlMkYlM0U=[/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="custom-block-1"][vc_column][vc_empty_space height="20px"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" el_class="custom-subblock"][vc_single_image image="703" alignment="center" el_class="custom-block-img"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>WORK WITH ME</h2>\r\nA 2-hour session, face-to-face in London or on the phone/Skype, to get crystal clear on what’s important to you and the choices you need to make to move into action and get what you want.[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="READ MORE" style="flat" shape="square" color="purple" size="xs" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fswitchedon.addwebprojects.com%2Fwork-with-me|title:Work%20with%20me|target:%20_blank"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" el_class="custom-subblock"][vc_single_image image="703" alignment="center" el_class="custom-block-img"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>BELIEFS</h2>\r\nMaking shit happen, Laughter until mascara runs down my cheeks, The incredibleness of the universe, Bright colours and sparkly things, Stretching my comfort zone.[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="READ MORE" style="flat" shape="square" color="purple" size="xs" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fswitchedon.addwebprojects.com%2Fbeliefs|title:Beliefs|target:%20_blank"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" el_class="custom-subblock"][vc_single_image image="703" alignment="center" el_class="custom-block-img"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>WHAT IS COACHING</h2>\r\n<div>Imagine you wanted to learn to ride a bike and you had the choice between a therapist, a consultant and a coach. How do you decide which one is best for you?</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="READ MORE" style="flat" shape="square" color="purple" size="xs" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fswitchedon.addwebprojects.com%2Fservices|title:What%20is%20coaching|target:%20_blank"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row fullwidth="1" el_class="custom-slider-home2"][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1455609527388{padding-right: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}"][rev_slider_vc alias="home-page-2"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_height="yes" fullwidth="1" el_class="custom-slider-home2"][vc_column][vc_row_inner el_class="custom-slogan-home"][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text]"Life is full of beauty. Notice it. Notice the bumble bee, the small child, and the smiling faces.\r\nSmell the rain, and feel the wind. Live your life to the fullest potential, and fight for your dreams."\r\n\r\n<strong>- Ashley Smith</strong>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="custom-blog-home"][vc_column][ewf-headline title="Blog"][vc_basic_grid post_type="post" max_items="2" element_width="12" gap="5" item="745" grid_id="vc_gid:1455022352715-78306c61-8015-9" taxonomies="3, 4"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '569-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-02 09:53:23', '2016-03-02 09:53:23', '', 569, 'http://switchedon.addwebprojects.com/569-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
